The paper deals with learning problems and deep learning models, which are typically studied in the machine learning subfield of computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on stochastic mirror descent algorithms and their convergence, implicit regularization, and generalization properties. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also experiments on standard image datasets and network architectures, indicating a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and data structures (cs.DS).
